post_text:
The Salem School Board has approved a 2020 Fall Reopening Plan that will offer in-school instruction bearing in mind the safety and well-being of staff, students, and the community. For those unable or unwilling to return to school, a remote/distance learning option will be offered similar to the experience provided last spring.

Please visit our website to review the entire plan, discover important new safety protocols, and submit your questions in advance of a virtual parent town hall meeting on July 21.

Go to: https://sau57.org/fall2020

post_text:
Fall 2020 Planning Update

Preliminary guidance from the State of NH School Reopening Task Force is expected to be released at the end of June. However, our District administrators are already reviewing options for a return to school this fall. Working groups have been established to research and analyze anticipated health and safety guidelines and assess their viability. These findings, along with guidelines from the state task force, will be considered in the development of school reopening recommendations to be presented to the Salem School Board on July 14.

Read more here:
https://sau57.org/ld.php?content_id=55558486

Chopped Challenge Tonight!

SHS Culinary students are prepping for tonight's 4:30 pm cooking competition to be held in the Salem High School Culinary Arts kitchen.

The 2019 Chopped Challenge will include teams of three culinary students from six area high schools. Each will be paired with a NH Army National Guardsman and will be tasked with creating meals from MRE's supplied to them.

The event is being live streamed by Salem TV Production students and carried live on Facebook, SCTV-17, and the Seifert Performing Arts Center.

Tune in here at 4:30 pm:
https://www.facebook.com/ssdtv6

Competition details can be found here:
https://www.2019mrechallenge.com

post_text:
Ever thought of working in a school-year position or as a substitute for the Salem School District?

These positions may be the perfect opportunity for you. These positions provide parents with a schedule that is similar to your children’s schedule. Substitute positions can also be very flexible. We have opportunities at the elementary, middle, and high school levels for the following positions:

Full-Time and Part-Time Positions:
• Assistants (Instructional Classroom and Non-Instructional)
• Custodian (full-year position)
• School Nurse
• Teacher (Long-Term Substitutes)

Substitutes:
• Teachers
• Assistants (Instructional Classroom and Non-Instructional)
• Nurses
• Custodians
• Food Service Workers
• Administrative Assistants

Interested? Please visit our website at www.sau57.org/human-resources/employment for further information and to complete an on-line application.

Woodbury School
October 22, 2019 at 6:41 AM ·

Massive results and records fell at Saturday's NH D1 Cross Country Championships! Your girls' team are now back, to back, to back state champs! The last time that happened in NH was 1978! Gabby Martiniello won the solo title back to back, the first Woodbury athlete to ever do so! The boys team also took the state title (first Woodbury boys win since 1983) and did it with a scoring top 5 of underclassman, so are already the heavy favorites to repeat in 20-21! #salempride

Link to the event page is in the comments below with photos and interviews!

Once again, the Salem School District is offering a variety of enrichment opportunities for all students, Grades K-12, during the break. Sessions are held mornings and afternoons at various times from June until August.

Register today (enrollment is limited):
https://sau57.org/summerprogram

post_text:
This morning, weather forecasters moved up the anticipated start time for snow in our area. Snow is expected to begin by 2:00 p.m. Dismissing early is not an easy decision given parents limited preparation. Nevertheless, it will be prudent for all parents to prepare for a possible early dismissal today.

A decision will be made and conveyed before 11:00 a.m. this morning as the circumstance becomes more clear.

Thank you for your understanding.
